                       "message":  "W08-2-KEYCODE-PARITY: shell-local KeyCode-\u003eShortcut translation + keyboard/menu parity guard\n\nSecond carve of the accelerator-execution thread (design pass W08.2), on top of\nthe W08.1 canonical menu source (#308). Adds the shell-local keyboard -\u003e\nmenu-accelerator translation and a parity guard locking the editor-shell keyboard\nmap to the canonical menu, BEFORE any live input rewiring. No behaviour change:\nEditorKeyCommand::from_key_press stays the live executor (the keystroke cutover is\nW08.3).\n\n- NEW lifecycle/accelerator.rs: keycode_to_shortcut(KeyCode, ctrl, shift) -\u003e\n  Option\u003cShortcut\u003e, the rge_input::KeyCode + ctrl/shift -\u003e rge_editor_ui Shortcut\n  bridge. It lives in editor-shell (not editor-ui) because editor-ui cannot depend\n  on rge-input (forbidden-dep rule 4); editor-shell depends on both. Exhaustive\n  over KeyCode (letters -\u003e Key::Char uppercase, digits -\u003e Key::Digit, F-keys -\u003e\n  Key::Function, edit/nav/arrows -\u003e named Keys, the eight modifier keys -\u003e None).\n  pub via `pub mod accelerator` (mirrors EditorKeyCommand) so the not-yet-wired fn\n  is real public API, not dead code.\n- Parity test keyboard_map_and_menu_agree_on_shared_accelerators: drives BOTH\n  EditorKeyCommand::from_key_press and default_editor_menu().command_for_shortcut\n  with the same (KeyCode, ctrl, shift) and asserts they resolve the same logical\n  command for the four EditorKeyCommand-routed shared binds (Ctrl+S/Shift+S/Z/Y).\n  Pins the two intentional asymmetries: Ctrl+O routes via the inline window_event\n  arm (from_key_press -\u003e None, menu -\u003e OpenFile); Ctrl+2/0/4 time-scale binds are\n  execution-only (menu -\u003e None). Any future divergence fails the test.\n- lifecycle/mod.rs: `pub mod accelerator;` + `pub use accelerator::keycode_to_shortcut;`.\n\nNo live keyboard-path change, no Cargo/edge change, no EditorKeyCommand/menu change.\nGate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints; editor-shell accelerator tests (4) pass.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
