                       "message":  "W08-2-KEYCODE-PARITY: correct module doc — four EditorKeyCommand binds agree, Ctrl+O is the inline-open asymmetry\n\nCodex review on #309: the accelerator.rs module header (and the parity test\u0027s\nlead comment) claimed `from_key_press` and the menu resolver agree on FIVE\nshared accelerators including Open. Ctrl+O has no EditorKeyCommand bind\n(`from_key_press` -\u003e None); it routes via the inline `window_event` arm while the\nmenu maps it to OpenFile, so Open is one of the pinned ASYMMETRIES, not an\nagreeing bind. The test already modelled this correctly — only the prose was\nwrong.\n\n- Module header: \"agree on the four EditorKeyCommand-routed shared accelerators\n  (Save / Save-As / Undo / Redo)\"; Ctrl+O described as the inline-open / menu\n  OpenFile asymmetry alongside Ctrl+2/0/4.\n- Parity test lead comment: four binds resolve to the same command; Ctrl+O is a\n  fifth shared bind pinned separately below as the intentional asymmetry.\n\nComment-only; no code/test/behaviour change. fmt clean; accelerator tests 4/4.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
